<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7311&amp;p=71879#p71879"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Glitching A/V using GameGenie - help decoding]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7311&amp;p=71879#p71879"><![CDATA[
Looks like you'd have a lot of fun with Rom Corruptor.<br /><br />Anyway, a cheat finder lets you search for values in RAM that have changed a particular way.  For example, you search ram for the number of lives remaining, and you find it after you die several times.  Then you set a data breakpoint on that value, so the debugger stops at the code that takes away a life.  Replace the DEC or STA or whatever instruction it uses with some NOPs and you have infinite lives.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Dec 24, 2010 9:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
